Class RestRequestHandler<T>

      • getArguments

        public final List<String> getArguments(RestRequest request)
        Returns arguments of the provided request. E.g. if the request is "POST /b1/a1/a2/" and binding is "POST /b1/" then arguments are "a1" and "a2".
        Parameters:
        request - RestRequest dispatched to this RestRequestHandler.
        Returns:
        List that contains String arguments of the provided request. The returned List is empty if there are no arguments.

      • getBinding

        public final RestRequest getBinding()
        Returns string representation of the family of RestRequests this RestRequestHandler is able to handleRequest. Such a family of RestRequests is also a RestRequest and is called a binding. More strictly binding is a RestRequest that represents the biggest common part of all RestRequests this RestRequestHandler is able to handleRequest. E.g. if the RestRequestHandler is able to handleRequest requests "POST /elements/by_date/2014/01/30/" and "POST /elements/by_date/1985/" then binding is "POST /elements/by_date/".
        Returns:
        Returns string representation of the binding.

      • getServer

        A Server this RestRequestHandler belongs to.
        Throws:

      • handleRequest

        protected abstract CompletionStage<T> handleRequest(RestRequest request,
                                                    ExecutorService executorService)
        Handles the specified request. This method MUST NOT perform blocking operations.
        Parameters:
        request - RestRequest to handleRequest.
        executorService - ExecutorService to use to handleRequest the request. Implementation MUST NOT shut down this ExecutorService.
        Returns:
        CompletionStage that represents result of request handling. The returned CompletionStage MUST be completed exceptionally as follows:
        • with RestRequestHandlingException if handling of the request has failed
        • with BadRestRequestException if the request is incorrect
